Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity if the payment form is an ordinary annuity.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value of an Annuity} &=\$13,500\times\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{\left(1+0.068\right)^5}}{0.068}
\\[10pt]
&=\$13,500\times\dfrac{0.28031287
}{0.068}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$55,650.35}
\end{aligned}$$

**Based on our calculation, the present value of the annuity, if the payment form is an ordinary annuity, is $55,650.35.**

Now, let's calculate the future value if the payment is an ordinary annuity.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{FV of Oridnary  Annuity} &=\$13,500\times\dfrac{\left(1+0.068\right)^5-1}{0.068}
\\[10pt]
&=\$13,500\times\dfrac{0.389492681}{0.068}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$77,325.75}
\end{aligned}$$

**Hence, as can be seen in our calculation, if the payment is an ordinary annuity, the future value is $77,325.75.**
